PostgreSQL:
===========
- Database: healthpay
- Container: dokku.postgres.healthpay
- User: postgres
- Password: <your_postgres_password>
- Port: 5432

=== RESTORE INSTRUCTIONS ===

For MySQL:
  mysql -u mysql -p < [database_name]_full_dump.sql

For PostgreSQL:
  psql -U postgres < postgres_healthpay_dump.sql

=== SECURITY NOTES ===

1. Never commit actual credentials to version control
2. Use environment variables for production
3. Store credentials in secure vaults (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
4. Rotate credentials regularly
5. Use encrypted connections (SSL/TLS)
6. Implement least privilege access

